[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

We all know you will open 1\S with this hand. And after partner responds 1NT what is your next bid? 

With 6 of them you can rebid \Ss but you are too strong to say just 2\S. Your 17 points puts you in the Medium range where you make a jump. So you bid 3\S and partner bids 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:6.AQJ98.AK85.KQJ K754.63.62.T8532 AT2.K752.743.A97 QJ983.T4.QJT9.64"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1H pass 3H pass 4NT pass 5H pass 6H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "a7a1e6bf113d4ee85ca32153b46604823b7265d5d0e199952d1578110ec3b929"]
[Category "Basic Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "basic_bidding/major_suit_openings"]
[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

This is a big hand. But not quite enough to open 2\C. So you open 1\H and partner responds 3\H. Now what? 

You might bid 4\D as a slam try, but it is probably just as well to go ahead and ask for Aces. So you bid 4NT and partner owns up to holding 2 Aces. What is your next bid? 

You have all the Aces but don't go crazy. Partner only has 11-12 points so don't think too Grand! Bid 6\H.}

